                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Free legal aid
          OUR LEGAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Dec. 9: The National Legal Services Authority has said it will provide free assistance to victims of the Mumbai terror attack and families of security personnel who died or were injured combating the militants.         
	It said the families could get the legal aid for claiming compensation, medical treatment, death certificates and legal heir certificates.         
	The State Legal Services Authority will organise legal aid cells with a sitting or retired judicial officer, two or more lawyers and counsellors.                                                                                                                                                                          
